The paper discusses the integration of network coding and opportunistic routing in wireless mesh networks, which falls under the category of networked systems and communication (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the challenges and optimization techniques associated with this integration, which could fall under information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the performance evaluation of existing joint protocols, which could fall under systems and control (cs.SY) and multimedia (cs.MM).
